<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-31-1174 </DOCNO><TEXT>A method of 2-stage recording of radionuclide ventriculography has beenproposed, the second stage being shifted to a certain time interval,i.e. a delay line is introduced between a synchronizing device and computer.Particular attention is drawn to a choice of delay time depending ona computer memory volume: in a small memory volume delay time must beapproximately one-third of the patient's R-R interval.</TEXT></DOC>